  {
    "type": "h2",
    "text": "FINAL SUMMARY",
    "id": "h.p8w4lcv8aos7",
    "html": "<span class=\"c11 c6\">&nbsp;FINAL SUMMARY</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span>DFT ensures </span><span class=\"c19 c6\">testable silicon<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span>Scan design is </span><span class=\"c19 c6\">heart of DFT<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Fault modeling enables detection<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Controllability + Observability are key<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Scan stitching &amp; reordering are critical for PD</span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "h2",
    "text": "1️⃣ ATPG – Automatic Test Pattern Generation",
    "id": "h.jqks4z8ffoyz",
    "html": "<span class=\"c11 c6\">1️⃣ ATPG – Automatic Test Pattern Generation</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "What is ATPG?",
    "id": "h.hsd337kzwaas",
    "html": "<span class=\"c9 c6\">What is ATPG?</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "ATPG is a software tool that automatically generates test vectors to detect faults in a design.",
    "html": "<span>ATPG is a software tool that </span><span class=\"c6\">automatically generates test vectors</span><span class=\"c0\">&nbsp;to detect faults in a design.</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "Why ATPG is needed?",
    "id": "h.e2rdszljoui3",
    "html": "<span class=\"c9 c6\">Why ATPG is needed?</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Millions of faults exist in large chips<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Manual test writing is impossible<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">ATPG:<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c7 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Generates patterns<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c7 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Maximizes fault coverage<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c7 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Minimizes test time<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "ATPG Uses:",
    "id": "h.zb9pzb9fskjj",
    "html": "<span class=\"c9 c6\">ATPG Uses:</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Scan chains<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Fault models (stuck-at, transition)<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">DFT logic<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "img",
    "src": "images/image7.png",
    "alt": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "h2",
    "text": "2️⃣ Types of Scan Design",
    "id": "h.z3iwm7o2x3h9",
    "html": "<span class=\"c11 c6\">2️⃣ Types of Scan Design</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "1. Full Scan",
    "id": "h.qz6ipuo3c8g4",
    "html": "<span class=\"c9 c6\">1. Full Scan</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">All flip-flops are scan-enabled<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Highest fault coverage<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Most common in industry<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "2. Partial Scan",
    "id": "h.j69o5vffivem",
    "html": "<span class=\"c9 c6\">2. Partial Scan</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Only some flip-flops are scanned<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Used when:<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c7 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Area is critical<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c7 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Performance is critical<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "img",
    "src": "images/image10.png",
    "alt": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "h2",
    "text": "3️⃣ Shift Cycle vs Capture Cycle (VERY IMPORTANT)",
    "id": "h.rnjmkbb35rj7",
    "html": "<span class=\"c11 c6\">3️⃣ Shift Cycle vs Capture Cycle (VERY IMPORTANT)</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "Shift Cycle",
    "id": "h.o32sc4j6e8z",
    "html": "<span class=\"c9 c6\">Shift Cycle</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Scan Enable = 1<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Flip-flops act as shift registers<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Data shifted in/out<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "Capture Cycle",
    "id": "h.j6jf83lh184",
    "html": "<span class=\"c9 c6\">Capture Cycle</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Scan Enable = 0<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Functional clock applied<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Circuit response captured<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "Test Operation Flow",
    "id": "h.yrl959rtjwdw",
    "html": "<span class=\"c9 c6\">Test Operation Flow</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Shift → Shift → Shift → Capture → Shift out",
    "html": "<span class=\"c16\">Shift → Shift → Shift → Capture → Shift out</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "img",
    "src": "images/image1.png",
    "alt": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "h2",
    "text": "4️⃣ Scan Clock vs Functional Clock",
    "id": "h.bgm6rhzg27kw",
    "html": "<span class=\"c11 c6\">4️⃣ Scan Clock vs Functional Clock</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "Functional Clock",
    "id": "h.v18f4zw158vu",
    "html": "<span class=\"c9 c6\">Functional Clock</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Used during normal operation<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">High frequency<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "Scan Clock",
    "id": "h.fj1g15m4oidj",
    "html": "<span class=\"c9 c6\">Scan Clock</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Used during testing<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Low frequency (to reduce power)<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "Why Separate Scan Clock?",
    "id": "h.mis8uyahcg5f",
    "html": "<span class=\"c9 c6\">Why Separate Scan Clock?</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Avoid IR drop<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Avoid overheating<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Safe shifting<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "h2",
    "text": "5️⃣ Reset in Scan Design",
    "id": "h.wr59krr6g2s8",
    "html": "<span class=\"c11 c6\">5️⃣ Reset in Scan Design</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "Why Reset is Important?",
    "id": "h.499nfku8sg6y",
    "html": "<span class=\"c9 c6\">Why Reset is Important?</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Initialize flip-flops<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Avoid unknown (X) states<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "Types of Reset",
    "id": "h.hgp2nqg0zy6j",
    "html": "<span class=\"c9 c6\">Types of Reset</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Asynchronous reset<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Synchronous reset<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "p",
    "text": "Reset must be scan-friendly",
    "html": "<span>&nbsp;Reset must be </span><span class=\"c19 c6\">scan-friendly</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "img",
    "src": "images/image2.png",
    "alt": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "h2",
    "text": "6️⃣ Multiple Scan Chains",
    "id": "h.e0pnv6r77k1y",
    "html": "<span class=\"c11 c6\">6️⃣ Multiple Scan Chains</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "Why Multiple Scan Chains?",
    "id": "h.o9gycee7mhi",
    "html": "<span class=\"c9 c6\">Why Multiple Scan Chains?</span>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Single chain = very long shift time<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c3 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Multiple chains:<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "ul",
    "html": "<li class=\"c2 c7 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Reduce test time<br></span></li><li class=\"c2 c7 li-bullet-0\"><span class=\"c0\">Parallel shifting<br></span></li>"
  },
  {
    "type": "hr"
  },
  {
    "type": "h3",
    "text": "Example",
